  "texts": [
    "This can address the current lack of explicit academic integrity policies and guidelines on using new AI-powered technologies in higher education institutions (Perkins & Roe 2023).",
    "Moreover, our findings can be used in the design of intervention programs that can strengthen the important principles of integrity while empowering learners and educators in the effective use of these tools.",
    "AI-powered Digital Writing Tools (AI-DWTs), a term we interchangeably use with ADWTs, are not new to learners and educators.",
    "For decades, they have evolved in sophistication to offer different assistance across varying writing task requirements.",
    "Thanks to Natural Language Processing (NLP)."
  ]
